</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0279-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0279-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Letter not found.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0279-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0279-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>Thomas Montgomerie registered the power of attorney from Mrs. Savage in the Fairfax County court on 17 April. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0222&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-08-02-0222-fn-0001#GEWN-02-08-02-0222-fn-0001" class="document">Bryan Fairfax to GW, 16 April 1770, n.1</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0279-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0279-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Perhaps after he received George Mercers letter of 18 Dec., GW found it easier to entertain the notion that fear of her husband was responsible for Mrs. Savages seemingly erratic behavior.</p>

</div>
